def univariate_plots():
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(7, 2, figsize=(18,27))
    axx = 0

    for feature in features :
        sns.distplot(cData[feature], bins=8, ax=axes[axx][0]);
        psn = sns.boxplot(cData[feature], ax=axes[axx][1])
        
        
        xl = feature.title() + ' - ' + str(axx)
        psn.set(xlabel=xl)
        axx+=1
    plt.show()
    
univariate_plots()

Feature Engineering¶

Dealing with Outliers¶

Imputing outliers with median¶

Replacing outliers with NaN to impute with the mean¶

cData = original.copy() cData.slag.replace(cData.slag.max(), np.nan) cData.water.replace(cData.water.max(), np.nan) cData.fineagg.replace(cData.fineagg.max(), np.nan)

imputer = SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.nan, strategy='median') imputer = imputer.fit(cData)

In [15]:
for col_name in cData[features].columns:
    q1 = cData[col_name].quantile(0.25)
    q3 = cData[col_name].quantile(0.75)
    iqr = q3 - q1
  
    low = q1-1.5*iqr
    high = q3+1.5*iqr
    cData.loc[(cData[col_name] < low) | (cData[col_name] > high), col_name] = cData[col_name].median()

Checking for complexity of the model

In [20]:
#function to review model complexty 
def linearRegressionComplex(myDegree):
    pftrs = PolynomialFeatures(degree = myDegree)
    x_poly = pftrs.fit_transform(Xtrain)
    predict_ = pftrs.fit_transform(Xtest)

    cmr = LinearRegression()
    cmr.fit(x_poly, ytrain)
    crm_pre = cmr.predict(predict_)
    crm_r2 = r2_score(ytest, crm_pre)
    return crm_r2

Check different models and tune the best one¶

In [22]:
def getFoldedModelScores(name, model, num_folds, xtr, xts, ytr, yts):
    seed = 7
    global results
    kfold = KFold(n_splits=num_folds, random_state=seed)
    res = cross_val_score(model, xtr, ytr, cv=kfold)
    model.fit(xtr, ytr)
    pre = model.predict(xts)
    r2 = r2_score(ytest, pre)
    dd = {'Method':name, 'meanScore':res.mean()*100, 'stdScore':res.std()*100, 'r2':r2}
    results = results.append(dd, ignore_index=True)

getFoldedModelScores('DTreeRegressor', DecisionTreeRegressor(), nfolds, Xtrain, Xtest, ytrain, ytest)
getFoldedModelScores('Ridge', linear_model.Ridge(alpha=.5), nfolds, Xtrain, Xtest, ytrain, ytest)
getFoldedModelScores('Lasso', linear_model.Lasso(alpha=0.1), nfolds, Xtrain, Xtest, ytrain, ytest)
getFoldedModelScores('ElasticNet', linear_model.ElasticNet(random_state=0), nfolds, Xtrain, Xtest, ytrain, ytest)
getFoldedModelScores('BayesianRidge', linear_model.BayesianRidge(), nfolds, Xtrain, Xtest, ytrain, ytest)
getFoldedModelScores('RandomForestRegressor', RandomForestRegressor(), nfolds, Xtrain, Xtest, ytrain, ytest)

def ShowImportance(importance, myColumns):
    ft = pd.DataFrame(importance, columns=['Importance'], index=myColumns).T
    sns.barplot(data=ft)
    ft
In [25]:
def showModelPerformance(model, xtr, xts, ytr, yts):
    y_pred = model.predict(xtr)
    print('Performance on training data: ', model.score(xtr, ytr))
    print('Performance on testing data:  ',  model.score(xtr, ytr))
    print('R2 score: ', r2_score(ytr, y_pred))

In [31]:
# configure bootstrap
values = xyData.values
n_iterations = 1000        
n_size = int(len(xyData) * 1)    

stats = list()   
for i in range(n_iterations):
    # prepare train and test sets
    train = resample(values, n_samples=n_size)  # Sampling with replacement 
    test = np.array([x for x in values if x.tolist() not in train.tolist()])  # picking rest of the data not considered in sample
    
    
     # fit model
    dtr = grid_search.best_estimator_
    dtr.fit(train[:,:-1], train[:,-1]) 
    # Take the target column for all rows in test set

    y_test = test[:,-1]    
    # evaluate model
    # predict based on independent variables in the test data
    score = dtr.score(test[:, :-1] , y_test)
    predictions = dtr.predict(test[:, :-1])  

    stats.append(score)
In [32]:
plt.hist(stats)
plt.show()
# confidence intervals

# 95% confidence
alpha = 0.95                             
p = ((1.0-alpha)/2.0) * 100
lower = max(0.0, np.percentile(stats, p))  
p = (alpha+((1.0-alpha)/2.0)) * 100
upper = min(1.0, np.percentile(stats, p))
print('%.1f confidence with a interval of  %.1f%% and %.1f%%' % (alpha*100, lower*100, upper*100))

95.0 confidence with a interval of  86.4% and 92.3%
